OL,3,CMinimum wage increases for millions as
OL,4,Cbusiness taxes rise
OL,6,FFrom Tuesday, the national living wage
OL,7,Fincreased for everyone employed aged
OL,8,F21 and over, giving a pay rise of up
OL,9,Fto #1,400 over the course of a year,
OL,10,Fbased on a 35-hour working week.
OL,12,FUnder the 6.7% rise people will be
OL,13,Fpaid #12.21 an hour, 77p more than the
OL,14,Fcurrent living wage of #11.44.
OL,16,FFull-time workers can expect to make
OL,17,F#26 more a week, and #117 more a
OL,18,Fmonth, the Government said.
